@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->New" "Project->New"
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Creating a new project window."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}New@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Creates a new project names "Untitled".

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  There is a limit on the number of open projects available.  A requester will appear if the maximum is reached.
  A "default" icon can be created by saving it as "Untitled" in Iconian 3's working directory.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Open..." "Project->Open..."
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Loading an existing icon."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Open...@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Loads an icon from disk into the currently selected project.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  If the icon is a Newicon with both old and new images, a second window will open to hold the Newicon images.
  Multiple icons may be selected.  The first icon will be placed into currently selected project.  Projects will be opened to receive icons after the first.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Open New..." "Project->Open New..."
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Using an existing icon to create a new project window."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Open New...@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Combines the @{"Project->New" link "Project->New"} and @{"Project->Open..." link "Project->Open..."} menu items into a single entry.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Restore" "Project->Restore"
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Restoring an icon from disk."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Restore@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Attempts to reload the original icon from disk.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Save" "Project->Save"
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Saving an icon."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Save@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Stores the current project to disk, using the current project name.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  Selecting this while the filename is still "Untitled" will overwrite any "default" icon on disk.  Care should be used.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Save As..." "Project->Save As..."
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Saving an icon using a different name."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Save As...@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Prompts for a filename, under which the current project will be saved.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  If an icon exists under the selected filename, a requester will appear.  Choosing "Merge" will copy the selected project's icon images into the selected file.  Any tooltypes, icon and window positions will be preserved.  This requester may be turned off from the @{"Windows->Open->Settings..." link "Windows->Open->Settings..."} window.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Close" "Project->Close"
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Closing a project window."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Close@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Closes the currently selected project.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  If the selected project has been modified, this action must be confirmed.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Export" "Project->Export"
@TOC "Project"
@next "Project->Buffer Size"
@Keywords "Saving an icon as source code."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Export@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Saves a diskobject structure as source code.  Code may be saved as either Assembler, C or E.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  This code has not been tested for any language.  Also, this function is incomplete, and only saves the image structures.
@ENDNODE
