@NODE "Project->NewIcons" "Project->NewIcons"
@PREV "Project->Icon Save Mode" "Project->Icon Save Mode"
@NEXT "Project->Iconify" "Project->Iconify"
@TOC "Project"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}NewIcons@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Controls for NewIcon support.

@{b}Subitems@{ub}
  @{"Save" link "Project->NewIcons->Save"}
  @{"Save As..." link "Project->NewIcons->Save As..."}
  @{"Seperate Palettes?" link "Project->NewIcons->Seperate Palettes?"}
  @{"Mark as Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard"}
  @{"Dot is Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard"}

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  This menu item may be unavailable if you do not have NewIcons installed on your system.  To access NewIcon support, obtain an archive from Aminet, Fred Fish CD, or any good Public Domain supplier.  The newicon.library is NOT supplied with the Iconian package.

@{b}See Also@{ub}
  @{"NewIcons" link "NewIcons"}
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->NewIcons->Save" "Project->NewIcons->Save"
@TOC "Project->NewIcons"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}NewIcons@{ub}
 Sub:	@{b}Save@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Similar in function to @{"Project->Save" link "Project->Save"}, but stores the icon as a NewIcon.  The old (standard) images are controlled by @{"Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard"} and @{"Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard"}.

@{b}See Also@{ub}
  @{"NewIcons" link "NewIcons"}
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->NewIcons->Save As..." "Project->NewIcons->Save As..."
@TOC "Project->NewIcons"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}NewIcons@{ub}
 Sub:	@{b}Save As...@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Similar in function to @{"Project->Save As..." link "Project->Save As..."}, but stores the icon as a NewIcon.  The old (standard) images are controlled by @{"Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard"} and @{"Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard"}.

@{b}See Also@{ub}
  @{"NewIcons" link "NewIcons"}
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->NewIcons->Seperate Palettes?" "Project->NewIcons->Seperate Palettes?"
@TOC "Project->NewIcons"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}NewIcons@{ub}
 Sub:	@{b}Seperate Palettes?@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  When checked, each icon image will support it's own, customizable palette.  When an image is the current one, the screen will change reflect this palette.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  This option is only available when Iconian 3 is running on it's own screen.

@{b}See Also@{ub}
  @{"NewIcons" link "NewIcons"}
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard" "Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard"
@TOC "Project->NewIcons"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}NewIcons@{ub}
 Sub:	@{b}Mark as Standard@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Flags the current project as the default images for NewIcons.  Only the images and save modes will be used.

@{b}See Also@{ub}
  @{"Dot is Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard"}
  @{"NewIcons" link "NewIcons"}
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard" "Project->NewIcons->Dot is Standard"
@TOC "Project->NewIcons"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}NewIcons@{ub}
 Sub:	@{b}Dot is Standard@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Signals that NewIcons will not contain a standard image.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  Only use this option if you are planning on always using NewIcons.  Also, do not use this if you are planning on redistributing the icons.  At the very least, use the internal tool/project images supplied by Commodore.

@{b}See Also@{ub}
  @{"Mark as Standard" link "Project->NewIcons->Mark as Standard"}
  @{"NewIcons" link "NewIcons"}
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Iconify" "Project->Iconify"
@PREV "Project->NewIcons"
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Iconifying Iconian 3."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Iconify@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Places Iconian in a hidden mode.  Double-clicking on Iconian's appicon will restore the program.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  Dropping icons on Iconian's appicon will also restore the program.  These icons will be opened as new projects, if room is available.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->About" "Project->About"
@TOC "Project"
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}About@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Brings up a requester that displays author, copyright, version and registration information.
@ENDNODE
@REM -----------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "Project->Quit" "Project->Quit"
@TOC "Project"
@Keywords "Quitting Iconian 3."
Menu:	@{b}Project@{ub}
Item:	@{b}Quit@{ub}

@{b}Function@{ub}
  Stops the program.

@{b}Notes@{ub}
  Disposal of any modified projects must be confirmed before this function actually quits.

  Closing the last open project window will also quit the program.
@ENDNODE
