@NODE "Bugs" "Bugs, Errors, and Other Stuff."
@TOC main
@KEYWORDS "Problems you should know about."

@{b}Error levels:@{ub}
  1. @{b}Minor@{ub} - Usually a visual problem and not serious.
  2. @{b}Medium@{ub} - This may cause problems if you are not careful.
  3. @{b}Serious@{ub} -  A problem that may crash the machine.
  4. @{b}SEVERE@{ub} - Uh oh!  It's guaranteed to piss you off!

3. Selecting a style other than plain for the window font will cause MagicCX's menu-2-cycle feature to lock the machine.

3. Using the MENU-HELP feature seems to lock up the machine occasionally.  I can't track the problem down.  Until I do, I suggest using the "MAIN" and "MENUS" pages to access menu help.

2. Magic Menus doesn't seem to like a few things I do with the menus.  As I've had nothing but frustration in the past with Magic Menus, I suggest you remove it from your system.  All manipulations of the menus are system legal, where as what Magic Menus does is not.  It is your choice.

1. The status line will overwrite the borders if the magnification window is too small..  Sorry!

1. MagixCX's menu-2-cycle seems to ignore gadget help messages.

3. I'm having problems with ReqTool's CallBack hook.  Use SMARTREFRESH if Iconian is crashing after popping up requesters.
@ENDNODE

